  "type": "mcq",
  "title": "Electric potential on conducting surface",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><include href=\"../Passage/VR024049.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Assuming that the electric potential is zero an infinite distance from the conductor, which of the following statements is true about the magnitude of the electric potential at points <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Y</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i4",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It is greater at point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> than at point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Y</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It is greater at point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Y</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> than at point <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It is zero at both points <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Y</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It has the same nonzero value at both points <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>X</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>Y</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">There is not enough information to determine at which point, if either, the magnitude of the electric potential is greater.</p>",
        "value": "i5"
      }
    ]
  },
